@northernfrancehanone @Thalia the Graceful I'll look into it...thank you both. I had no clue I maybe had an answer for how I feel somewhere in reach all along. It...really means the world that two strangers would stop by to help, especially thinking that I've been scared of people and figured I'd just be bullied and...yeah...I'll look into it, I've been crying and can't really give an answer one way or another yet but this somehow gives me so much hope.

@ateminana It's not our place nor our right to say for you if you are trans or not. I'm only giving you a heads up as I wish people gave me one sooner. You have however raised some red flags considering what you said and the doujin you've been reading and also what you added afterward.
I can tell you one thing I'm sure of though, don't deny yourself whoever you might be trans or not for other people, it will never be enough for them and your life will be miserable becaude of it. I can only encourage you to explore and find some answers for yourself. Maybe go to egg_irl, it's a meme reddit for people that don't know they are trans, maybe you will recognize yourself there and if you don't you will maybe at least have a laugh.

@ateminana Trust me when I say absolutely no one wants to be trans. And I once learned that wanting to be a girl is the same thing as being one on the inside. And my advice is to stay in the closet until you feel safe enough to come out. Maybe tell a few close friends how you feel if you know they don't mind.

@Thalia the Graceful The thing is I've always wished I was a girl but I'm too scared to think about what it'd mean to be trans. I don't want to get bullied and made fun of, but you already get so much shit for even looking the slightest bit gay, let alone wanting to be a girl. I feel stuck, like I can't stand being in this body but I can't stand the thought of all the bullying and hatred that I'm gonna get if I don't stick with it and force myself to be a dude...

@ateminana Trust me. I'm trans and used to think exactly like you before I realized. Cis guys don't want to be girls at all. And if asked about what they'd do if this happened to them, masturbating is probably their only answer.
@northernfrancehanone Not sarcastic. I didn't think that's what being trans felt like, doesn't everyone want to be a girl? It's objectively better?
